<?xml version="1.0" standalone="yes"?>
<!DOCTYPE PLUGIN [
<!ENTITY name "statsview.plus">
<!ENTITY author "Alexander Phillips">
<!ENTITY version   "2026.04.07.12">
<!ENTITY launch "Settings/StatsViewPlusSettings">
<!ENTITY github "alexphillips-dev/StatsView-Plus">
<!ENTITY pluginURL "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/&github;/dev/&name;.plg">
<!ENTITY source "/boot/config/plugins/&name;/&name;">
<!ENTITY MD5 "93090059ec95a742b3bb4e266e63b39f">
]>
<PLUGIN name="&name;" author="&author;" version="&version;" launch="&launch;" pluginURL="&pluginURL;" min="6.12.0" icon="circle-chart.png" support="https://github.com/&github;/issues">

<CHANGES>
##StatsView Plus

###2026.04.07.12
- Fix: Revert System Stats to the original working realtime chart behavior after the later bootstrap changes failed on live Unraid
- Fix: Add page-level System Stats boot diagnostics so missing assets or init failures render a visible on-page error with the reported reason

###2026.04.07.11
- Fix: Revert the seeded realtime System Stats bootstrap that could leave the Stats view blank on load
- Fix: Add a visible System Stats init failure banner instead of allowing a silent blank page

###2026.04.07.10
- Fix: Restore the System Stats page after the realtime chart bootstrap regression introduced a blank render
- UI: Seed realtime charts with a Highcharts-safe baseline so traces appear immediately without unsupported options

###2026.04.07.09
- UI: Seed realtime System Stats charts with an initial baseline so traces render immediately instead of appearing empty on first load
- UI: Enable visible realtime point markers in the System Stats panels so low-activity charts still show live movement

###2026.04.07.08
- Maintenance: Scrub legacy developer attribution from the live repository metadata and packaged manifest
- Maintenance: Republish the dev package after the provenance scrub so the current archive and feed no longer carry the removed references

###2026.04.07.07
- UI: Replace the legacy System Stats screen with a new commander-style dashboard that matches the Disk Stats command view
- UI: Add compact control panels, live summary cards, realtime telemetry panels, session peaks, and command-center sidebars for CPU, memory, network, and storage
- Backend: Add a dedicated `system_dashboard` payload and version-aware page assets so the new System Stats screen owns its own render path and update behavior

###2026.04.07.06
- UI: Compress the Disk Stats command view again with tighter spacing, smaller cards, slimmer meters, and denser fleet/watchlist rows
- Maintenance: Add version-tracked asset URLs and no-cache page headers so fresh installs and upgrades pick up the latest Disk Stats assets immediately
- Maintenance: Record the installed plugin version during install and trigger a one-time page refresh when the backend detects newer frontend assets

###2026.04.07.05
- UI: Tighten the Disk Stats command-center layout with smaller cards, denser fleet rows, lighter panel spacing, and reduced headline scale
- UI: Compress the hero, summary grid, sidebar panels, chips, utilization rails, and watchlist blocks so the page fits more data on screen at once

###2026.04.07.04
- UI: Replace the legacy Disk Stats Highcharts screen with a new command-center dashboard layout
- UI: Add live fleet cards, watchlist panels, utilization rails, threshold markers, and responsive dashboard styling for Disk Stats
- Backend: Add a dedicated `disk_dashboard` JSON payload so the Disk Stats view can render modern array, pool, flash, and threshold data cleanly

###2026.04.07.03
- UI: Ship the plugin with the new `circle-chart.png` icon asset
- UI: Replace the old font-awesome page header icons with the shared plugin PNG across Stats, Settings, System Stats, Disk Stats, and System Information

###2026.04.07.02
- Maintenance: Add a dedicated dev branch feed plus branch-aware build and release automation
- Maintenance: Switch packaged updates to versioned archives so dev and main can publish independently

###2026.04.07.01
- Rename plugin to StatsView Plus
- Point manifest and support metadata to alexphillips-dev/StatsView-Plus
- Package source for standalone installation from the new repository

###2025.11.14
- Migrate repository to Unraid

